# Security

## HTTP hardening

- `helmet()` enabled
- CORS allowlist via `CORS_ORIGIN` — no wildcard with credentials in production
- `trust proxy` when behind reverse proxy
- `express.json({ limit: "1mb" })`
- Rate limiting: `generalLimiter` + `authLimiter` on auth routes

## Input

- Zod validation on all mutating endpoints
- Prisma parameterized queries only — no interpolated `$queryRaw`
- Sanitize user-provided strings before logging

## Auth secrets

- JWT secrets ≥ 32 chars from env
- Argon2id for passwords with configurable cost
- Hash refresh/OTP/reset tokens before storage

## Prevent

- SQL injection (Prisma + no raw interpolation)
- IDOR (ownership checks in services)
- Mass assignment (explicit Zod schemas, no spread of `req.body` into Prisma)

## Responses

- Never return stack traces in production
- Never expose internal paths or config in error messages

## Dependencies

Run `npm audit` in CI; pin versions; no untrusted packages without review.
